multiflexi-web (2.5.0) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Add tasks.php — task overview with metric cards, daily fulfilment chart,
    state distribution pie chart, and DataTables-powered task listing
  * TaskMetricsCards: 6 cards (Total, Fulfilled, Late, Failed, Missed, Active)
    with today's success percentile on the Fulfilled card
  * TaskSuccessChart: 14-day daily fulfilment rate line chart (SVGGraph)
  * TaskStateChart: all-time state distribution pie chart
  * TasksTable: filterable task table with state-coloured rows, links to job
    detail, RunTemplate, and Company pages
  * MainMenu: add Tasks to the Logs dropdown
  * CredentialForm: universal availability badge for credential types without a
    custom UI helper (calls checkAvailability() on the prototype, renders
    Bootstrap 5 alert + details panel)
  * RuntemplateRequirementsChoser: live availability badge on each assigned
    credential card (✅ / ⚠️ / 🔴 / 🚫 / ℹ️ keyed to CredentialState)
  * ExitCode: map exit code 75 (EX_TEMPFAIL / credential blocked) → 'warning'
  * CompanyJobLister: add job-credential-blocked row class for exit code 75

 -- vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Sat, 14 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0200

multiflexi-web (2.4.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Pre-Depend on multiflexi-common so the 'multiflexi' user (created by its
    preinst) always exists before this package's postinst chowns the web files
    (fixes intermittent "chown: invalid user: 'multiflexi:www-data'" install
    failures, e.g. on Ubuntu jammy, which blocked the whole build matrix)
  * Add company-level RBAC access filtering across dashboard lists/charts
  * Hide Admin menu for unprivileged users and filter company dropdown
  * Add read-only notice and server-side protection for company-user assignment
  * Add activation wizard deep-link support (?company=... -> step 2)
  * Improve DataTables paging defaults and backend length limits for stability

 -- vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Sat, 06 Jun 2026 12:20:00 +0200

multiflexi-web (2.4.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Migrate the whole web interface from Bootstrap 4 to Bootstrap 5
    (Bootstrap 5 CSS; convert popovers, modals, badges, button groups,
    btn-block and directional utilities to their BS5 equivalents).
  * Upgrade DataTables to 2.2.2 with Buttons 3.2.2 (was an incompatible
    3.0 beta with mismatched Buttons 1.5.6); add ext.features.register
    polyfill and graceful JSON error handling in ajax2db.php.
  * Modernise the UI: dark navy navbar, card headers, high-contrast tables,
    redesigned login/logout/password-recovery splash pages with a large
    background logo, and mobile responsiveness.
  * Make the main navbar compact and right-align the language switcher;
    render the navbar login form inline.
  * Exit code indicator now uses dark, high-contrast semantic colours and
    correctly classifies exit code 0 as success.
  * Fix the cookie consent banner (Bootstrap 5 form-switch) and verify
    consent saving end to end.
  * Migrate FaIcon usages to BsIcon (Bootstrap Icons) and load jQuery once.
  * Hide the first-administrator setup button once any user exists.
  * debian: multiflexi-web5 now Conflicts/Replaces/Provides multiflexi-web
    so only one web interface can be installed at a time.

 -- vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:35:41 +0200

